      "hypothesis": "In a quiet bear regime the downside drift is a slow discount-rate repricing, not a fear cascade: short-side 21-day momentum continuation carries positive expectancy, and its profitable legs are the ones coincident with elevated real-yield pressure and a steepening 5y2y curve. The tradeable side is structurally SHORT; long signals from the same primary should be near-noise and filtered by the meta.",
      "causal_story": "BEAR_QUIET is the valuation de-rating phase: rv stays unremarkable while price grinds lower \u2014 drift-dominated diffusion driven by an exogenous factor, not self-excited selling. The driver is duration repricing: when real_yield_5y_z252d is high, equity cash flows are discounted harder, producing persistent multi-week downside legs that a 21-bar momentum z-score (orthogonal to the 63-bar regime window) re-enters. us_5y2y_z252 ranks HIGHER here, marking late-cycle curve repricing that sustains legs; dxy_z252 (lower here) separates dollar-liquidity squeezes from pure rate legs; vix_chg_5 screens out fear-spike bars where quiet-bear continuation fails; volume confirms institutional participation. None are regime-defining.",
